<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="id77fbface-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I75" topic="referencesInText" id="id77fbfacf-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5">
<heading class="centered smallCaps">References in Text</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0"><ref href="/us/usc/t23/s204">Section 204 of title 23</ref>, referred to in subsec. (a), was repealed and a new section 204 enacted by <ref href="/us/pl/112/141/dA/tI/s1119/a">Pub. L. 112–141, div. A, title I, § 1119(a)</ref>, <date date="2012-07-06">July 6, 2012</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/126/473">126 Stat. 473</ref>, 489.</p>
</note>
</notes>
